fields.title: manali
fields.description: Manali is a picturesque hill station in Himachal Pradesh, nestled in the Beas River Valley. Surrounded by snow-capped peaks, lush forests, and apple orchards, it's a popular destination for honeymooners, adventure seekers, and nature lovers. Key attractions include Solang Valley, Rohtang Pass, and Hidimba Devi Temple.

fields.title: dharamsala
fields.description: Dharamsala, also in Himachal Pradesh, is known for its serene environment and Tibetan culture. It is the home of the Dalai Lama and the Tibetan government-in-exile. Set against the backdrop of the Dhauladhar mountains, it's famous for McLeod Ganj, Buddhist monasteries, and trekking trails like Triund.
